reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great show rack!
reviews.reviewText: This was easy to put together. It's not premium quality, but it doesn't feel crazy cheap either, and it looks great in my room.Set-up was very easy and took less than ten minutes.I can easily fit between 8 and 10 pairs of shoes on it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Baby shoes rack
reviews.reviewText: I bought this as a shoe rack for my baby (she currently wears infant size 3-4) I can fit 3 pairs per row. I would guess that largest shoe will still be toddler size. I don’t see this working for any adult sized shoes. It is also thin and delicate so not for heavy wear. It is however, perfect for what I needed. It’s small enough for my little ones shoes and low enough she can reach and pick the pair she wants to wear each day.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 30, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The pieces broke immediately once I started to assemble. I tried to tape the broken pieces and build the rest with my friend, but we both gave up when all the pieces kept cracking. I will have to throw out all the pieces and buy another shoe rack because this was very cheap and bad quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 7, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The directions for assembly are not very detailed. I suggest arranging the four end pieces the way they need to line up first, so you do not end up having to disconnect one corner to rearrange the end piece. It can take a little effort to squeeze the last corner together. But once assembled this unit works fine for what we need.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Ok for price
reviews.reviewText: Good for the price but ended up only have 3 shelves instead of 4 bc 3 of the little plastic pieces cracked while building it so wasn’t able to attach the final shelf.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Stronger than some relationships…
reviews.reviewText: Look, I have 4 kids and 6 dogs. This shoe rack sits at my entry way and is used and abused on a daily basis. For a good while, it housed one of the steps of my runners off my truck after it got torn off during an off road adventure.Muddy shoes, boots, bags, purses, dog accessories, sometimes even an actual dog.. who knows. This little rack doesn’t look like it would withstand the torture it’s been through but it doesn’t even have a scratch. And I’ve had it for a few months now before writing this review.Honestly, I wasn’t planning on writing a review for this because I really didn’t think it would last longer than a week in my house. Boy was I wrong!Oh, it was also really easy to assemble and fits a good amount of shoes (and other items).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I needed a small shelf for my kitchen in a smaller area, to get my crockpots and slo cooker off the floor. It works great! Glad I bought this!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Way too flimsy!
reviews.reviewText: Terrible to put together. Bends very easily. Super flimsy. There is not enough room to put shoes with any kind of height in the middle of it. But, it is very light weight and once you get it FINALLY put together it works nicely for flats.

I am very disappointed with this shoe rack. I bought this particular product because I wanted a white one that was quite narrow. This was priced well and fitted my criteria. As I was assembling it, many of the plastic connectors cracked and fell apart. That was disappointing enough, but I got to the end of the assembly process and found there were 2 connectors missing so I couldn’t add the “handles” at the top. I am left with a shoe rack that looks decent from a distance, but with all the cracked connectors holding it together I doubt it will last long.
